Shinylive render-cache patch (py-shiny-site)
============================================

Memoizes the shinylive Quarto filter's subprocess calls to
.quarto/shinylive-cache/ so a full-site render pays each identical call once
instead of once per document. See PR:
https://github.com/posit-dev/py-shiny-site/pull/382

The patched shinylive.lua is committed; this patch exists so that
`make quarto-extensions` (which re-downloads the pristine upstream extension)
can re-apply the change. If it stops applying, upstream changed: re-port the
cache block to the new shinylive.lua, then regenerate this file with

    git diff <pristine-ref> -- _extensions/quarto-ext/shinylive/shinylive.lua

(where <pristine-ref> is a commit holding the unpatched upstream copy) and
keep this header. If upstream ships its own caching, delete this patch and
the `git apply` step in the Makefile instead.

